Produced since 1994, Neige is the leading inspiration of La Face Cach?e de la Pomme. It is the very first ice cider (also known as apple ice wine) to be commercialized in Qu?bec and throughout the world. Neige R?colte d'Hiver ? produced from a variety of apples that do not fall during the autumn season ? is available in a limited edition series of 5866 bottles for the 2007 harvest. Edition 2008 is limited at 10 560 bottles. Picked between December and January, while the temperature was approximately -15?C, the fruits still hanging on trees were dehydrated by the sun and literally cooked by the cold and wind. Sugars were concentrated through natural cryoextraction. Frozen apples were then pressed in order to extract the precious nectar. The extracted must was then placed in stainless steel tanks where it fermented for a period of approximately eight months, at low temperatures, before being bottled.
